dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.

dcterms:description: Tiny-ImageNet consists of 64x64 color images from 200 classes, with each class containing 500 training images, 50 validation images, and 50 test images. It is used for visual recognition tasks.
